China has set a GDP growth target of 5.5 percent for 2022. To get an insight into how the National People's Congress (NPC) deputies view the country's economic development, CGTN reporter Su Yuting spoke to Li Dongsheng, an NPC deputy and chairman of the board of electronics company TCL Group. Li said this year's growth target reflects the resilience of China's economy. He also said that China's manufacturing sector should adapt to the impacts brought by the reconstruction of the global economic pattern.